snippet.textDisplay:
Wow...this is a much needed recap. Loved it every moment. My list of top 5 and the special one:
1. Faasle - Kaavish & QB
2. Bol - Shafqat Amanat Ali
3. Baanware - Shuja & Aima
4. Ranjish hi sahi - Ali Sethi
5. Katay na katey re - Aima, Rachel, Humera
And then HUM KYUN CHALEY USS RAH PAR.....the anthem!!!
Thank you CSP for spreading love through your beautiful presentations. Its a boon and a blessing for the music lovers across the world to witness such a gesture of promoting hidden and forgotten songs on such a unique platform of youth, energy and respect!
Bilal and Faisal - the face of STRINGS and their support staff....you guys are the actual heroes! Without your passion and perseverance, such an epic show would not have been possible. Everyone can create and recreate songs - but not everyone can present them in such a manner that they are loved, respected and admired by all.
Have been following CSP from Season 2...with each season, you guys have upped the presentation. There's nothing 'over the top' and there's nothing 'plain and bland'. The perfect balance between glitz, soberness, sincerity and lyrical originality has been retained...and thats what makes CSP so very special. Have been sharing your songs and the BTS too (I just love the way you guys interact BTS) with everyone in India. Please bring Kaavish, QB, Aima, Shuja, Sara Haider, Natasha Khan, Humera and ofcourse Shafqat Amanat Ali in CSP Season 11 again.  Salute, love and respect from India. Looking forward to Season 11.

snippet.textDisplay: Wow, Coke Studio, 10 years of great music and artistic integrity.  Congratulations from a fan in Canada.  I first found Coke Studio in Season 3 thanks to Tina Sani's "Nawai Ney" which was broadcast between programs on local TV.  What a wonderful season that was and I'm glad to see that when I've returned to Coke Studio over the years I see the great music continuing.  I've spent some time watching Coke Studio India too, but CS Pakistan remains the main one for me.  I truly wish I could attend some of the sessions some day.  Thanks for the wonderful experience and may another great 10 years be possible.
